{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Base","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease base and sides of a tart tin (Ø 22 cm) generously with butter.","Place graham crackers and sugar in mixing bowl then crush <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Add butter and mix <b>7 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to prepared tin. Use hands or a spoon to press crumb mixture firmly into base and up sides of tin to form an even, compact layer.","Bake for 10 minutes (180°C) then leave to cool in tin. Leave oven on to bake filling."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place lime peel and sugar in mixing bowl then grind <b>40 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg yolks in mixing bowl and whisk <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Without measuring cup, mix <b>2 min\/speed 4<b> while slowly adding condensed milk through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Add lime juice and reserved lime sugar mixture then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Pour pie filling into cooled base then bake for 15 minutes (180°C).","Leave to cool to room temperature, then cover with cling film and place in fridge for at least 4 hours before slicing and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Base","content":["255 g graham crackers","30 g sugar","140 g unsalted butter, diced, plus extra for greasing"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["2 limes, thin peelings of skin only","1 Tbsp sugar","4 egg yolks, from large eggs","1 tin sweetened condensed milk (approx. 397 g)","100 g lime juice, freshly squeezed"]}],"id":"r400914","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-HVWPoWZquQc\/XZWdYr_eYJI\/AAAAAAAAekw\/IM2l9Q8XLqkn52nnfqY0LBm335MAU__gACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Fq6tuR9D-07pUlVR.png","title":"Key Lime Pie","publishedAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6 g","fat":"17 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"45 g","calories":"1469 kJ \/ 351 kcal"},"usefulItems":"tart tin (Ø 22 cm), cling film, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Leftover egg whites can be used to make a meringue topping for the pie or for meringues.","To just cover base with crumb mix instead of base and sides, reduce graham crackers to <b>170 g<b> in <b>step 2<b> and butter to <b>100 g<b> in <b>step 3.<b>","Key lime pie can be topped with a dusting of icing sugar, whipped cream, caramel sauce, chocolate sauce or fruit coulis."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","4h 40m","12 slices"]}